\section*{Mechanism of Ab-mediated injury in type II hypersensitivity Rxn}
A. Complement-dependent rxns that leads to lysis of cells or render them susceptible to phagocytosis.
B. In ADCC, IgG-coated cells are killed by cells that bear Fc receptors for IgG (e.g. natural killer (NK) cells and macrophages)
C. Anti-receptor antibodies disturb the normal functions of receptors. In the following example, acetylcholine receptor antibodies impair neuromuscular transmission in myasthenia gravis
