\section*{Tests for type III hypersensitivity.}
1. Immunofluorescence tests for the detection of antigens, antibodies, Complement and immune complexes in tissues.
2. Detection of antibodies to suspected antigens such as horse serum proteins, spores, pigeon dropping antigens etc.
3. Tests for immune complexes in the serum

\section*{Summary.}
- Hypersensitivity reaction is an undesirable excessive immune reaction to antigens that ends up destroying host tissue.
- Can be managed by eliminating the trigger (pathogen or stimuli)
- Type II= antibody-mediated cytotoxic reaction.
- Type III= immune complex mediated reaction.
